==English==

===Etymology===
* First attested around 1400.
* {{suffix|account|able}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ʌˈkaʊntəbl̩/}}, {{X-SAMPA|/V"kaUnt@b@l/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ə.ˈkaʊn.tə.bəl/}}
* {{audio|En-us-accountable.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Having [[accountability]] (individuals have accountability); answerable.
#: {{usex|Every man is '''accountable''' to God for his conduct.}}
#: {{usex|You will be held '''accountable''' for your misdemeanors.}}
# Requiring accountability (property or funds require accountability).
# Liable to be called on to render an account;
# Being answerable for.
# Being liable for.
# {{context|rare|lang=en}} Capable of being accounted for; explicable; explainable.
#* {{quote-book|passage=True religion . . . intelligible, rational, and '''accountable''', -- not a burden but a privilege.|author={{w|Benjamin Whichcote}}}}

